# Update and Migration Lifecycle

- Treat updates as compatibility-sensitive: preserve existing behavior by default.
- Add explicit version checks for one-time migrations and make them idempotent.
- Separate install/upgrade routines from runtime request handling.
- For data shape changes, provide migration logic and safe fallback reads.
- Mark deprecated hooks/functions with clear alternatives and maintain shims when possible.
- Include rollback strategy for risky updates (feature flags, reversible migrations, guarded writes).
- Document upgrade-impacting changes in changelog/release notes before shipping.
- Validate updates against fresh install and upgrade-from-previous-version scenarios.
